%S A395446 1,0,0,0,552,302282,468698008
%N A395446 Number of Hamiltonian paths on an n X n grid, starting from a fixed corner cell and ending anywhere, where the allowed moves are (+-3,0), (0,+-3), or (+-2,+-2).
%C A395446 The 8 allowed moves are: 3 steps horizontally or vertically, or 2 steps diagonally (in all directions). Each cell must be visited exactly once. The path starts at a fixed corner cell and may end anywhere.This sequence arises from a traditional puzzle game played on paper in the Lombardy region (Italy), traditionally played on a 10 X 10 board.
%H A395446 Robert P. P. McKone, <a href="/A395446/a395446.txt">The a(5) = 552 Hamiltonian paths</a>.
%K A395446 nonn,hard,more,walk,new
